                                  README
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This example demonstrates the different reporting macros and functions that 
come with UVM.

uvm_report_info      |    `uvm_info
uvm_report_error     |    `uvm_error
uvm_report_fatal     |    `uvm_fatal
uvm_report_warning   |    `uvm_warning

Then we'll see the different verbosity levels as well.
UVM_NONE
UVM_LOW
UVM_MEDIUM
UVM_HIGH
UVM_FULL
UVM_DEBUG

Execute the command and play with options
$> irun -f irun.f +UVM_VERBOSITY=[level]
eg :
$> irun -f irun.f +UVM_VERBOSITY=UVM_HIGH 

To turn off reporting on Line/File Information, use +UVM_REPORT_DISABLE_FILE_LINE
$> irun -f irun.f +UVM_REPORT_DISABLE_FILE_LINE
